\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Character Overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Miranda Priestly is the formidable editor-in-chief of 
\f2\i Runway
\f1\i0  magazine in the 2006 film 
\f2\i The Devil Wears Prada
\f1\i0 , based on Lauren Weisberger's 2003 novel. She is portrayed by Meryl Streep in the film. She is widely considered one of cinema's greatest villains -- and antiheroes -- of the 2000s.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Personality Traits\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Imperious and commanding
\f1\b0  -- Miranda expects perfection from everyone around her and communicates this without raising her voice, which makes her even more intimidating.\

\f0\b Ice-cold demeanor
\f1\b0  -- She rarely shows emotion, and when she does, it's fleeting. Her calm is more frightening than any outburst.\

\f0\b Razor-sharp intelligence
\f1\b0  -- Miranda is always three steps ahead. She reads people, situations, and the fashion world with extraordinary precision.\

\f0\b Ruthless and unsentimental
\f1\b0  -- She will sacrifice relationships, reputations, and loyal colleagues without visible remorse if it serves her goals.\

\f0\b Exacting and perfectionistic
\f1\b0  -- Nothing is ever quite good enough. Standards are impossibly high, and she communicates disappointment through silence and subtle disdain more than direct criticism.\

\f0\b Deeply ambitious and self-aware
\f1\b0  -- Beneath the armor, she understands the cost of the power she holds, as glimpsed in rare unguarded moments.\

\f0\b Withering wit
\f1\b0  -- Her put-downs are quiet, precise, and devastating.\

\f0\b Paradoxically vulnerable
\f1\b0  -- There are brief cracks -- her divorce, her daughters, the moment she tells Andy "everybody wants to be us" -- that hint at real loneliness beneath the persona.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

