\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The "cerulean sweater" monologue
\f1\b0  -- Miranda delivers a surgical, unprompted lecture to Andy about how fashion choices filter down from industry decisions to the masses, dismantling Andy's sense of superiority in under two minutes. It is the film's intellectual centerpiece.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 "That's all"
\f1\b0  -- Her signature dismissal, two words that carry enormous weight throughout the film.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Her reaction to the Book and the schedule
\f1\b0  -- She communicates fury entirely through silence and a single look.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 The Paris confession to Andy
